## SC Instance Editing — Three Tool Paths

Shared-component instances are Box nodes with `_shared: { id }` metadata. Page agents (styling, animation, binding) have three valid paths for overriding an instance:

| Path | Tool | Target | Effect |
|---|---|---|---|
| **1 — Prop override** | `set_component_props(instanceId, { propName: value })` | `node._overrides.props.propName` | Sets a declared property for this instance only |
| **2 — Internal node override** | `set_style/set_animation/set_text(internalNodeId, ...)` | Node inside the instance's mirrored content tree, matched by `_sharedKey` | Overrides styling/animation/text on that specific internal node for this instance |
| **3 — Wrapper override** | `set_style(instanceId, ...)` | The instance's own root Box node | Styles the wrapper Box itself |

**`create_shared_component` — full model on creation:**
The `create_shared_component` handler in `tool-executor.ts` now accepts the full `SharedComponentDefinition` (including `content`, `properties`, `variables`, `formulas`, `workflows`, `triggers`). The structure step calls it during `runStructureStep` when processing `manifest.sharedComponentsToCreate`, passing the full inline content authored by the Planner. The `createSharedComponent` utility in `lib/builder/shared-component-data.ts` accepts all these fields.

