## `set_src` — Image vs Video Routing

- **Image nodes** → `store.patchProp(id, 'src', url)` → sets top-level `node.src`
- **Video nodes** → `store.patchProp(id, 'props.src', url)` → sets `node.props.src`

Renderer picks up both: `...(node.src && { src: node.src })` spread, falling back to `node.props.src` when top-level `src` is falsy.

---

## `set_text` / `set_text_color` — Child Targeting

Button-like `Box` nodes and `Link` nodes hold visible text in a **child** (`Text`, `LinkText`, `ButtonText`). Both `set_text` and `set_text_color` walk to the child before patching — never patch the wrapper's `text` or `className` directly. The check is structure-based: if the node has no own `text` property and has exactly one text-type child, the child is targeted automatically.

---

## Video Component Defaults

`primitive-components.ts` defaultNode and `add_video` executor both use:
```
autoPlay: true, loop: true, muted: true, controls: false
```
This is the correct ambient/embedded default for landing pages. Only override when the user explicitly requests a media player (`controls: true`).

---

## Class Conflict Prevention

When writing an arbitrary-value class for a property, always strip the corresponding `style.*` key, and vice versa. Also strip old-style shorthand classes (e.g. `p-4` when setting individual sides).

Common patterns:
```typescript
// Write class AND strip the inline style key
cls = `${cls} pt-[24px]`.trim();
removeNodeStyleKeys(store, nodeId, ['paddingTop']);

// Strip shorthand when setting individual sides
cls = cls.split(' ').filter(t => !/^p-/.test(t)).join(' ').trim(); // removes p-4, p-8, etc.

// Write arbitrary-px class AND strip all old scale tokens
cls = replaceTokenGroup(cls, ROUNDED_PREFIXES, 'rounded-[8px]');
// (borderRadius is not written inline — the class alone is authoritative)
```

